        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName>. <date>Oct. 27.
                1852</date></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Ed. Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">During the present political campaign<lb/> among our most prominent
                men are found some<lb/> of our creed the Hon. <persName>J. B. Benjamin</persName>.
                U. S. Senator<lb/> Elect, a whig, and Hon <persName>E. W. Morse</persName> State
                Elector,<lb/> and Ex-Speaker of the House of Representatives <add>a
                democrat</add>.<lb/> Many have assailed them by slurs upon their religious<lb/>
                tenets and I forward you the reply of the latter<lb/> gentleman to one of these
                petty attacks. It is<lb/> very beautiful and will be only appreciated<lb/> by all
                who have the good fortune to read it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I understand that some time ago<lb/> a similar document was
                transmitted relative<lb/> to an<del>whig</del> attack upon the Hon. <persName>J P.
                    Benjamin</persName>,<lb/> so you may see by this that it is no party
                feeling<lb/> alone, but a desire on both sides to underrate<lb/> political standing
                by the standard of Religion.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The extract is from the Courier of today<lb/> &amp; you will find it
                in the other page.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">I have the Honor</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">to be yr obt Sert.</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">Hen. J. Labatt</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
